ts run both the agent and native parts. I wonder if I need to modify the metadata at all. The main focus seems to be on test coverage rather than metadata, which might be generated externally. But if there's a failure in the native code due to the lack of a configuration for `java.util.EnumSet` fields, that’s worth some consideration. The active class's `locateField` is noteworthy too since it deals with `java.util.EnumSet` and `java.util.EnumMap` private field elementType.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_T14Sjv6QU5q6DBVZqCeEz1Gk|fc_0220c3bab18a8a360169f4ef7bd5c8819fb35992657c576712", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/src/test/java/org_apache_htrace/htrace_core/ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_htrace.htrace_core;\n\nimport java.util.EnumMap;\nimport java.util.EnumSet;\n\nimport org.apache.htrace.fasterxml.jackson.databind.util.ClassUtil;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest {\n    @Test\n    void findEnumTypeUsesLocatorForEmptyEnumSet() {\n        EnumSet<TraceState> states = EnumSet.noneOf(TraceState.class);\n\n        try {\n            Class<? extends Enum<?>> enumType = ClassUtil.findEnumType(states);\n\n            assertThat(enumType).isEqualTo(TraceState.class);\n        } catch (IllegalArgumentException | IllegalStateException e) {\n            assertThat(e).satisfies(ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest::isExpectedJdkFieldAccessFailure);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void findEnumTypeUsesLocatorForEmptyEnumMap() {\n        EnumMap<TraceState, String> statesByName = new EnumMap<>(TraceState.class);\n\n        try {\n            Class<? extends Enum<?>> enumType = ClassUtil.findEnumType(statesByName);\n\n            assertThat(enumType).isEqualTo(TraceState.class);\n        } catch (IllegalArgumentException | IllegalStateException e) {\n            assertThat(e).satisfies(ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest::isExpectedJdkFieldAccessFailure);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void isExpectedJdkFieldAccessFailure(RuntimeException exception) {\n        if (exception instanceof IllegalArgumentException) {\n            assertThat(exception).hasCauseInstanceOf(IllegalAccessException.class);\n        } else {\n            assertThat(exception).hasMessageContaining(\"Can not figure out type\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private enum TraceState {\n        STARTED,\n        FINISHED\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 704, "output": 1911, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32311, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777659748586, "responseId": "resp_0220c3bab18a8a360169f4ef652d38819f9a90cf49446955a3"}}
